Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Nitish Rana, out Caught by Pooran!! Caught behind appeal turned down and SRH review. There was a noise as the ball went past bat, was it bat hitting the ground? or the edge? Waiting for UltraEdge. There is spike and Nitish Rana has to go. Credit to Pooran for spotting the edge. He wanted the review to be taken. Full outside off, Nitish Rana backs away and drives, thin edge and then the bat hits the ground. UltraEdge picks up the murmur as the third umpire says and T Natarajan strikes. End of a good knock though. Nitish Rana c Pooran b T Natarajan 54(36) [4s-6 6s-2]

Commentary Text: Umran Malik to Shreyas Iyer, out Bowled!! Cracker and cleaned up. Umran Malik bowls out Shreyas Iyer with a fine yorker. Shreyas Iyer is moving all around the place, again makes room to go on the off-side but Umran Malik keeps his cool and fires in a yorker on middle and off, Shreyas Iyer fails to dig it out and the ball crashes low into the stumps. The SRH camp is thrilled with that wicket. That's what extreme pace can get you - wickets in the middle overs against set batters. Steyn and Murali have a big laugh and celebrate the wicket. From their celebrations, it looks like a plan which was hatched that has come off. Shreyas Iyer b Umran Malik 28(25) [4s-3]
